      <abstract>
        <p>Testimony of the 16-year old K.H. on the deportation of his family to Kamenets-Podolsk s
          in the summer of 1941, hiding in Kőrösmező/Yasina, finding shelter in a Jewish orphans’
          home in Budapest, his arrest and deportation to Auschwitz, his experiences in Buchenwald,
          the I.G. Farben (Brabag) synthetic fuel factory in Rehmsdorf and his liberation in
          Theresienstadt.</p>
      </abstract>
